item.title: Biden Lands in Israel to Meet Leaders on Hamas War
item.description: The president arrived a day after a deadly blast at a hospital in Gaza demonstrated the volatility of the conflict and heightened fears of escalation.

item.title: Metals Rise on Stronger China Economic Data
item.description: Base metals prices pushed higher as China data showed the economy fared better than expected in the third quarter, while safe-haven demand triggered by geopolitical tension kept gold prices elevated.

item.title: Oil Climbs on Rising Tensions in Israel-Hamas Conflict
item.description: Oil prices moved higher in Europe, with worries over the conflict in Gaza intensifying late Tuesday.

item.title: Dollar Edges Lower, Could Fall Further as Momentum Builds
item.description: The dollar was slightly lower, shrugging off higher Treasury yields and stronger-than-expected U.S. retail sales, and it could continue to drop as this weaker trend gains momentum, MUFG said.

item.title: Eurozone Bond Yields Rise, Lack Renewed Safety Bids
item.description: Eurozone government bond yields rose in early trading, extending Tuesday’s moves in the absence of a renewed safety bid, according to analysts.

item.title: China's Economy Gets Boost From Stimulus, but Headwinds Grow
item.description: China’s economy is likely to struggle for a while yet, economists say. Real estate remains a major risk and consumer confidence is fragile.

item.title: Handelsbanken Tops Hopes as Income Rises
item.description: Handelsbanken posted a third-quarter profit that beat expectations, as net interest income rose to SEK12.2 billion, but said the slowdown in the economy and higher interest rates caused growth in deposit and lending volumes to level off.

item.title: Volvo Sees Lower Truck Market Levels in 2024
item.description: Volvo posted forecast-beating third-quarter earnings but said order intake fell 27%, reflecting a normalization of demand, with truck markets seen weakening next year.

item.title: U.K. Inflation Holds Steady
item.description: Consumer prices in the U.K. rose 6.7% in September, matching the previous month’s rise and complicating the task of the BOE as it looks to keep bringing inflation down.

item.title: ABB's 4Q Guidance Seen Below Expectations
item.description: ABB’s guidance for the fourth quarter came in slightly below consensus expectations, which may result in minor downward revisions, Citi said.

item.title: ABB Misses Views; Sees Improved Fourth Quarter
item.description: ABB reported third-quarter profit and revenue below forecasts, but said it expected an operational core earnings margin of around 16% and higher revenue growth in the final quarter of the year.

item.title: Tele2 Keeps Outlook as Third Quarter Meets Hopes
item.description: Tele2 posted third-quarter results largely in line with expectations, with underlying earnings up 3%, and maintained its full-year and midterm guidance.

item.title: ASML Sees Flat Revenue in 2024
item.description: ASML said it sees 2024 as a transition year, expecting revenue to be similar to 2023, given uncertainty around the demand recovery in the semiconductor industry.

item.title: Tech Leaders Say AI Will Change What It Means to Have a Job
item.description: Artificial intelligence will likely lead to seismic changes to the workforce, eliminating many professions and requiring a societal rethink of how people spend their time.

item.title: Just Eat Lifts Profit Outlook Despite Slower Sales
item.description: Just Eat Takeaway.com raised its full-year earnings guidance, but cautioned that gross transaction value was expected to fall around 4% this year compared with a previous forecast for growth of between negative 4% and positive 2%.

item.title: WSJ Tech Live 2023: Tech Leaders Discuss the World-Changing Potential of AI, and Some of Its Risks
item.description: Open AI’s Sam Altman, Meta’s Chris Cox and others spoke at WSJ’s annual event.

item.title: Next Year Promises to Be Better For Bond Investors
item.description: Bond investors should enjoy much better returns in 2024 as economies weaken and central banks cut interest rates, AllianceBernstein told Dow Jones Newswires.

item.title: Nvidia, Foxconn to Develop New Class of Data Centers Focused on AI
item.description: Chip maker Nvidia is expanding its partnership with Taiwan’s Foxconn, and aims to develop a new class of data centers that can power artificial-intelligence services.

item.title: American Grandmother Stuck in Gaza After Visit to Ailing Father
item.description: A retired schoolteacher from Utah wants to go home, while U.S. deal to open border to Egypt is stalled.

item.title: Wall Street's Latest Obsession Is an Unknowable Number
item.description: The debate centers on the unobservable ‘term premium’ that models say is surging.
